<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Burner ignition is the #1 stove repair in LA &mdash; and it&rsquo;s often a $150&ndash;$200 job</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Gas stove burner ignition failure is the most common appliance repair call we receive across Los Angeles. A burner that clicks endlessly without lighting, or stopped igniting after a boilover, is almost always an igniter or spark electrode issue &mdash; not a gas valve or control board failure. Flat-rate pricing that assumes a worst-case scenario costs you more than the actual repair requires.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. The $89 fee covers the full diagnosis. After a boilover, the igniter module is often just wet &mdash; cleaning and drying resolves it with no replacement part at all. We check all burners while on site and test the oven cavity (if a range-style stove) before leaving. Gas stove calls include supply pressure verification and post-repair leak check at no extra charge.</p>
      <p>Apartment stoves in LA &mdash; especially older GE, Whirlpool, and Hotpoint freestanding units common in Koreatown, Silver Lake, and Mid-Wilshire rentals &mdash; are a significant portion of our stove calls. These are almost always worth repairing. A burner igniter replacement on an older unit costs far less than a landlord replacing the whole stove.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-label">&#9888; After a boilover &mdash; try this first</div>
      <p>If a burner stopped igniting right after a boilover, remove the burner cap and grate and let everything dry completely &mdash; sometimes 24 hours. Clean the igniter tip with a dry toothbrush. If the burner still won&rsquo;t light after drying, call us. We&rsquo;ll confirm whether it&rsquo;s a wet igniter or an actual component failure before ordering any parts.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="transparency-block">
      <div class="tr-card them">
        <h3>Flat-Rate BlueBook pricing</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
