    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does stove repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor typically runs $150&ndash;$380 for standard brands. Burner ignition issues &mdash; the most common call &mdash; run $150&ndash;$280 and often require no replacement part at all. Parts are quoted separately. The $89 diagnostic fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">My gas burner won&rsquo;t ignite after a boilover. How much to fix?</div><div class="faq-a">Boilover-caused ignition failures are the most common stove call in LA. The igniter is often just wet. We clean and test before assuming a part is needed. Total can be as low as $61 if no part is required &mdash; as shown in the Silver Lake example above.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. After diagnosis we quote the specific part needed as a separate line item. Gas stove calls include supply pressure verification and post-repair leak test at no extra charge. OEM parts used wherever available.</div></div>
